i-reference/audio/voice-consent-object?lang=node&utm_source=openai))\\n- If you want, I can also give you:\\n  - a version using the **official OpenAI Python SDK**\\n  - an example that uploads from a **web request / FastAPI**\\n  - a script that converts audio to `.ogg`/Opus first"\n}'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': 'Всё ясно. Реализация простая:\n- Голосовое сообщение в Telegram — это `.oga`/`.ogg` файл (Opus codec)\n- Скачиваем байты через существующий `download_file_base64` (или напрямую)\n- Отправляем в OpenAI Whisper `/v1/audio/transcriptions`\n- Получаем текст → передаём как обычный текст сообщения\n\nПишу реализацию:', 'tool_calls': [{'id': 'toolu_017KiUUavFv6dQPrdh8Fyqmg', 'function': {'arguments': '{"prompt": "I need to add voice message (Telegram voice notes) support to the supervisor. The changes are:\\n\\n1. **In `supervisor/telegram.py`**: Add a `download_file_bytes` method to `TelegramClient` that downloads a Telegram file and returns raw bytes (instead of base64). Also add a standalone `transcribe_voice` function that takes audio bytes and an OpenAI API key, sends them to OpenAI Whisper API (`whisper-1` model at `https://api.openai.com/v1/audio/transcriptions`) and returns the transcribed text (or None on failure).\\n\\n```python\\ndef download_file_bytes(self, file_id: str, max_bytes: int = 25_000_000) -> Tuple[Optional[bytes], str]:\\n    \\"\\"\\"Download a file from Telegram and return (raw_bytes, file_path). Returns (None, \'\') on failure.\\"\\"\\"\\n    try:\\n        r = requests.get(f\\"{self.base}/getFile\\", params={\\"file_id\\": file_id}, timeout=10)\\n        r.raise_for_status()\\n        data = r.json()\\n        if not data.get(\\"ok\\"):\\n            return None, \\"\\"\\n        file_path = data[\\"result\\"].get(\\"file_path\\", \\"\\")\\n        file_size = int(data[\\"result\\"].get(\\"file_size\\") or 0)\\n        if file_size > max_bytes:\\n            return None, \\"\\"\\n        download_url = f\\"https://api.telegram.org/file/bot{self._token}/{file_path}\\"\\n        r2 = requests.get(download_url, timeout=30)\\n        r2.raise_for_status()\\n        return r2.content, file_path\\n    except Exception:\\n        log.warning(\\"Failed to download file_id=%s bytes from Telegram\\", file_id, exc_info=True)\\n        return None, \\"\\"\\n```\\n\\nAnd the transcribe function (module-level, not a method):\\n```python\\ndef transcribe_voice(audio_bytes: bytes, file_path: str, openai_api_key: str) -> Optional[str]:\\n    \\"\\"\\"Transcribe voice audio bytes using OpenAI Whisper API. Returns text or None.\\"\\"\\"\\n    if not openai_api_key or not audio_bytes:\\n        return None\\n    try:\\n        # Determine filename from file_path extension\\n        ext = file_path.rsplit(\\".\\", 1)[-1].lower() if \\".\\" in file_path else \\"oga\\"\\n        filename = f\\"voice.{ext}\\"\\n        mime_map = {\\"oga\\": \\"audio/ogg\\", \\"ogg\\": \\"audio/ogg\\", \\"mp3\\": \\"audio/mpeg\\",\\n                    \\"mp4\\": \\"audio/mp4\\", \\"m4a\\": \\"audio/mp4\\", \\"wav\\": \\"audio/wav\\",\\n                    \\"webm\\": \\"audio/webm\\", \\"flac\\": \\"audio/flac\\"}\\n        mime = mime_map.get(ext, \\"audio/ogg\\")\\n        files = {\\"file\\": (filename, audio_bytes, mime)}\\n        data = {\\"model\\": \\"whisper-1\\"}\\n        headers = {\\"Authorization\\": f\\"Bearer {openai_api_key}\\"}\\n        r = requests.post(\\n            \\"https://api.openai.com/v1/audio/transcriptions\\",\\n            headers=headers, files=files, data=data, timeout=30,\\n        )\\n        r.raise_for_status()\\n        text = r.json().get(\\"text\\", \\"\\").strip()\\n        return text if text else None\\n    except Exception:\\n        log.warning(\\"Failed to transcribe voice message\\", exc_info=True)\\n        return None\\n```\\n\\n2. **In `supervisor/main_loop.py`**: In the `_process_updates` method, after extracting image data and before the check `if not text and not image_data: